The paper deals with a problem of firefighting on graphs, which involves placing firefighters on vertices to prevent the spread of fire and save a critical subset of nodes. This problem is related to graph theory (cs.DS) and game theory (cs.GT), as well as algorithms and complexity (cs.AI) and computational geometry (cs.CG). The paper also introduces new concepts related to important separators and tight separator sequences, which could fall under the sub-category of social and information networks (cs.SI).
